2. Technical Architecture
The system follows a client-server architecture where the frontend interacts with the backend Flask application, which processes requests and manages application data.
2.1 Frontend
The frontend of the system is built using:
• HTML templates rendered using Flask
• CSS for styling and responsive design
• JavaScript for interactive components
• Glassmorphism UI design for modern interface appearance
The interface includes pages such as:
• Home Page
• Patient Login & Registration
• Doctor Login
• Patient Dashboard
• Doctor Dashboard
• AI Health Assistant
Figure 2: User Login Page
 2.2 Backend
The backend is implemented using the Flask web framework in Python.
Key responsibilities of the backend include:
• Handling HTTP requests and routing
• Managing user authentication
• Processing appointment bookings
• Storing and retrieving patient and doctor data
• Running the AI health analysis module
Important backend modules include:
•app.py — Main Flask application that handles all routes, user authentication, appointment booking, diagnosis submission, and directly communicates with AWS DynamoDB and SNS. All database logic is built into this single file — no separate database module is needed.
2.3 Database
The system uses a JSON-based storage system to manage application data.
Instead of a traditional relational database, structured JSON files are used to simulate database operations.
Data is stored in the following files:
• patients.json – Stores patient information
• doctors.json – Stores doctor profiles and availability
• appointments.json – Stores appointment booking records
• diagnoses.json – Stores diagnosis records created by doctors
The backend uses Python's json module to read and update these files.
