5. AWS Integration
The system is designed to support deployment on Amazon Web Services (AWS).
Cloud services used include:
•	AWS EC2 – Hosts the Flask application on an Ubuntu server, making MedTrack accessible online via a public IP address
•	AWS DynamoDB – NoSQL cloud database that stores all user accounts (UsersTable) and appointment records (AppointmentsTable)
•	AWS SNS (Simple Notification Service) – Sends automatic email notifications to users whenever a new appointment is booked
•	AWS IAM (Identity and Access Management) – Manages secure access control, ensuring only the EC2 instance has permission to access DynamoDB and SNS resources
The cloud deployment enables the system to be accessible online and scalable for multiple users simultaneously.

